Right.   And it&#x27;s not just <i>that</i> the typing is static, but that you are <i>using</i> it properly.  Cf:<p><pre><code>    struct price { int value; };
    struct quantity { int value; };

    int placeOrderUnsafe(int price, int quantity);
    int placeOrderSafer(struct price, struct quantity);

    ...

    placeOrderUnsafe(quantity.value, price.value) /* does the wrong thing */
    placeOrderSafer(quantity, price) /* caught at compile */</code></pre>
